The aim of this workflow is to study the variation of near neighbor Heisenberg magnetic exchange tensor components of 2D GdI2 across:

  - Different supercell sizes (to check SC size convergence), 
  - Gd-Gd bonds,
  - Direction of moments in the surrounding bath

For the 4 states using the 4 state energy mapping method.

This ASE based workflow initializes VASP calculations and later execute them with a bash script.

Variations available:
    1. Tensor component             (Inp <string>    : xy, zz etc.  )
    2. One of 4 states              (Opt inp <string>: ud, dd etc.  )
    3. Direction of bath moments    (Inp <string>    : x,  y  etc.  )
    4. 2 selected atoms (J1/2/3 etc)(Opt inp <2 ints>: 3 1, 5 2 etc.)
    5. 2D Supercell to be created   (Inp <2 ints>    : 4 5, 3 4 etc.)

Files:

- prepare-4state-noncol.sh
main script to run with the above arguments. Min requirement: two integers for SC size

- POSCAR.3atom.transZ.cart.vasp
Unit cell structure in POSCAR format, used to create supercells using

- supercell.py

- run_leo.sh
Bash script to submit jobs for execution

- GdI2_4state-noncol.py
Main ase workflow to initialize the calculation

- toten.sh
Gather the energy and calculate the J values


ASE requirement:
Needs env var: VASP_PP_PATH
python
